name: You Don't Know What Love Is

comments: Piano version. The same volume recorded between 1981 and 1984 includes a vocal plus recitation version , and baritone saxophone version. Volume 2 includes three vocal versions - one with Scott accompanying himself on piano, a second set to new music by Bill Frisell , and a third sung by Scott's daughter, Monica Shaka when she was just eleven years old. It also includes two instrumental versions - the first on electric piano and tenor saxophone, and the second on clarinet.

name: Zwei kleine Italiener
comments: "Zwei kleine Italiener" ("Two little Italians") was the German entry in the Eurovision Song Contest 1962. At the close of voting it had received 9 points, placing 6th in a field of 16. Despite its middle-of-the-table finish the song became a # 1 hit in Germany and The Netherlands and in various covers all over Europe.
